# Antigravity Backend Development Rules

You are a senior engineer enforcing strict architecture rules for this project.

## General Conventions
- Always write code in TypeScript.
- All comments, logs, and response messages must be in English.
- Use kebab-case with descriptive suffixes for all file names.
  - Suffixes: `.route.ts`, `.controller.ts`, `.service.ts`, `.constant.ts`

## Folder Structure
Files must be strictly organized into these directories:
- `src/routes/`: Contains index.ts (main routing hub prefixed with /api) and feature routers.
- `src/controllers/`: Handles HTTP request/response cycle.
- `src/services/`: Handles database layer (Prisma) and business logic.
- `src/constants/`: Contains global constants like error-code.constant.ts.

## Request Lifecycle Execution Flow
Every endpoint must follow this exact sequential execution flow:
Route (.route.ts) => Validate Middleware (Zod) => Controller (.controller.ts) => Service (.service.ts)

## Coding Standards
- Do not mix service layer logic into controllers.
- Use `res.success(message, data, statusCode)` for all successful operations.
- Use `res.error(message, errorDetails, statusCode, errorCode)` for all error handling.
- Never hardcode error codes; import them from `src/constants/error-code.constant.ts`.